Thank you for your interest in Sacramento State!


This articulation agreement displays the lower-division courses required in the major: Sacramento State courses on the left and approved (articulated) transfer courses on the right. Although completion of the coursework listed below is not mandatory prior to admission, students are advised to complete as much lower-division course preparation as possible prior to transfer.


Additional Resources:

  • See the University Catalog for the full listing of degree requirements for this major.
  • Visit our Sac State Apply page for more information about our campus!
  • Visit the Admissions website for current transfer admission requirements.
  • Connect with an Admissions Counselor.

templateAssets.content:
1. Students must earn a "C-" grade or higher in all prerequisite courses and in all courses applied to the major.
  2. Mathematics students may select an emphasis in one of the following areas: Pure Mathematics, Applied Mathematics, Statistics, or Teacher Preparation Program.
  3. The Associate Degree for Transfer (ADT) in Mathematics is compatible with the B.A. in Mathematics at Sacramento State. Students pursuing the Associate Degree for Transfer must complete all lower-division major coursework with a "C" or better.
  4. STAT 1 is required for the emphasis in Statistics and for the Teacher Preparation Program.
  5. PHYS 11A and PHYS 11C are recommended courses for all Mathematics majors.
  6. For additional information, please visit: Department of Mathematics and Statistics.
